Defendant Sandra Lenora White in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Defendant Sandra Lenora White in custody.  Brandon Wigley on behalf of Paul M. Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.

Branch 17 accepts this case and scheduled for Sentencing on 10-19-2015 at 10:00 in branch 17 room 310 of safety building.

Defendant Sandra Lenora White in court with attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant has pending felony case before Branch 17.  The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance and State's motion, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Court will allow this case to be transferred to Branch 17 if Judge Stark is willing to accept jurisdiction.  Case adjourned to Branch 33.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 19, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Sandra Lenora White in court with attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC.

Any right of substitution begins to run as of the date of receipt of this notice, unless notified by the court on an earlier date.  Review hearing scheduled for September 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed, Justice Point Deferred Prosecution Agreement Progress Report.

Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 6.
